post_text:
Public Service Announcement: Holliston Drug and Alcohol Awareness Coalition Parent Support Group is a peer led group created for families that are dealing with addiction, recovery, and their effect on all of us. We are here not to offer professional advice, but to share our personal experiences, wisdom, strength, resources, and most importantly, hope. If you have a loved one suffering from the disease of addiction and need support, our group meets the third Tuesday of each month, 7:30 pm at Christ The King Lutheran Church, 600 Central St., Holliston. Your privacy and anonymity are respected.
For questions or further information please contact;
Jan @ (508) 527-6748

